From: chainonyourdoor <chainonyourdoor@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: upgrade BORE CPU scheduler v5.3.0 -> v6.8.0-rc1 algorithm (KABI-safe) for android14-6.1

Ports the algorithm-level improvements from firelzrd/bore-scheduler's
patches/testing/0001-linux6.12.37-bore-6.8.0-rc1.patch onto this
kernel's existing v5.3.0 KABI-safe backport. Upstream v6.8.0-rc1 targets
a 6.6+/EEVDF kernel; android14-6.1 is still CFS, so everything tied to
EEVDF internals (se->deadline, pick_eevdf(), RUN_TO_PARITY protect-slice
tunable, base_slice/min_base_slice) is NOT ported -- it has no CFS
equivalent. Only the scheduler-model-independent parts of the upgrade
are ported:

  - calc_burst_penalty(): switched to the clz-based log2p1 helper
    (16-bit fixed-point precision instead of the old 8-bit one)
  - new default tunables: sched_burst_penalty_offset 22->24,
    sched_burst_penalty_scale 1280->1536, sched_burst_cache_lifetime
    60000000->75000000
  - sched_burst_smoothness: single knob replacing the old split
    smoothness_long/short pair (same effective behavior: instant
    shrink, shifted growth)
  - 3-way inheritance (sched_burst_inherit_type: 0=none, 1=direct
    parent, 2=ancestor-hub) replacing the old on/off
    sched_burst_fork_atavistic toggle
  - NEW thread-group burst cache: CLONE_THREAD children now inherit
    from siblings in the same thread group, not just from the parent
  - NEW futex_waiting boost: a task blocked in futex_wait does not
    accrue burst penalty while blocked (kernel/futex/waitwake.c hook)
  - NEW stop_update guard around reweight_task() to prevent
    re-entrant update_curr() accounting while a priority change is
    being applied
  - dropped the separate sched_burst_exclude_kthreads toggle;
    kthreads are now always excluded from burst scoring, matching
    upstream v6.8.0-rc1 (no functional loss, it defaulted to 1/on)

KABI note: struct sched_entity's 4 existing ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE slots
(already fully consumed by the v5.3.0 patch) are reused for the new
fields too -- the byte budget still fits exactly:
  slot1 (u64):  burst_time                              [unchanged]
  slot2 (8B):   prev_burst_penalty(u16) + curr_burst_penalty(u16)
                + burst_penalty(u16) + stop_update(bool)
                + futex_waiting(bool)                    [was 4x u8]
  slot3 (u64):  child_burst_cache (packed bore_bc: 48-bit
                timestamp + 16-bit penalty)          [was child_burst
                                                       + child_burst_cnt]
  slot4 (u64):  group_burst_cache (packed bore_bc)   [NEW -- was
                                                       child_burst_last_cached]
No new task_struct fields were needed. (For the record: task_struct's
own ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(4)-(8) are also free in this tree, in case a
future addon needs task_struct-level KABI room -- BORE does not touch
them.)

NOTE: as with the original v5.3.0 patch, the hunks below reuse the
proven-working context from that patch (this sandbox still has no
network access to android.googlesource.com to test-apply directly).
bore.sh's forward/reverse --dry-run check still aborts the build loudly
on any mismatch instead of silently skipping BORE.

The kernel/futex/waitwake.c hunk is the one exception with the least
context confidence: it's carried over from firelzrd's mainline patch
rather than from this repo's own history, since no prior BORE patch in
this repo touched that file. If it fails to apply, bore.sh will catch
it (see above) -- the futex boost is a minor optimization and safe to
drop by removing that one hunk without affecting the rest of BORE.

Signed-off-by: chainonyourdoor <chainonyourdoor@gmail.com>
